        <enumvalue id="group__ieee802154_1gga34aecc5996174a812b295a3a4693ad09a38c67aac70d24b31996871fe4686d9ee" prot="public">
          <name>IEEE802154_CONFIG_AUTO_ACK_FPB</name>
          <briefdescription>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Indicates how radio driver should set Frame Pending bit in ACK responses for Data Requests. If enabled, radio driver should determine whether to set the bit or not based on the information provided with <computeroutput>IEEE802154_CONFIG_ACK_FPB</computeroutput> config and FPB address matching mode specified. Otherwise, Frame Pending bit should be set to <computeroutput>1</computeroutput>(see IEEE Std 802.15.4-2006, 7.2.2.3.1). </para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="group__ieee802154_1gga34aecc5996174a812b295a3a4693ad09ab897aea56ea5e9ddf306c5c0d75c2cd7" prot="public">
